The paper focuses on improving the performance of OpenCL kernels through compiler phase selection and ordering, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The use of iterative exploration and analysis of generated code also suggests a focus on performance optimization (cs.PF) and parallel computing (cs.DC). Finally, the evaluation of code-features and benchmark similarity suggests a potential application in system design and optimization (cs.SY).
